---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Redwood Outdoors or Almost Heaven better?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For most buyers, Almost Heaven is the better choice — lower price, longer warranty (5 years vs 1 year), and a 30-year track record. Redwood Outdoors wins on material quality: their Thermowood construction is more durable outdoors long-term than cedar, especially in wet or cold climates. If budget is flexible and you live somewhere with heavy rain, snow, or freeze-thaw cycles, Redwood Outdoors Thermowood is worth the premium."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much more does Redwood Outdoors cost vs Almost Heaven?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Significantly more. Almost Heaven's most popular model (Pinnacle 4-Person) starts around $2,199. Redwood Outdoors Thermowood models start around $6,600. That is roughly a $4,000 gap before heater and installation costs. For buyers who want the Thermowood material advantage without the full Redwood Outdoors price, there is no direct middle-ground competitor — it is effectively a choice between value and premium."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Base
  title="Redwood Outdoors vs Almost Heaven Sauna (2025): Which Should You Buy?"
  description="Redwood Outdoors vs Almost Heaven head-to-head. Price, materials, warranty, and who each brand is actually for. The honest comparison."
  canonical="/guides/redwood-outdoors-vs-almost-heaven"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">Redwood Outdoors vs Almost Heaven Sauna (2025)</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-500 mb-8">Updated January 2025 &mdash; Backyard Sauna Pro</p>

    <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
      <img src="/images/lifestyle/sauna-cabins-outdoor.jpg" alt="Outdoor barrel saunas side by side comparison" class="w-full object-cover max-h-80" loading="lazy" width="1200" height="800" />
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8 text-sm text-stone-700">
      <strong>Affiliate disclosure:</strong> As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This page may contain affiliate links.
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 mb-6">Two of the most-searched outdoor sauna brands in North America. Almost Heaven dominates on value and availability. Redwood Outdoors leads on material quality. Here is the full comparison so you can decide which matters more for your situation.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
      <table class="text-sm w-full">
        <thead>
          <tr class="text-left text-stone-500 border-b border-stone-200">
            <th class="pb-2 pr-6">Factor</th>
            <th class="pb-2 pr-6">Almost Heaven</th>
            <th class="pb-2">Redwood Outdoors</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-stone-700">
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Wood type</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">Western red cedar</td>
            <td class="py-2">Thermowood (heat-treated) or cedar</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Entry barrel price</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">~$1,599 (Refuge 2-person)</td>
            <td class="py-2">~$3,500 (cedar), $6,600+ (Thermowood)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Warranty</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">5 years structural</td>
            <td class="py-2">1 year</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Brand history</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">30+ years</td>
            <td class="py-2">Newer, fast-growing</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Amazon availability</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">Yes — Prime shipping</td>
            <td class="py-2">Direct only</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Outdoor durability</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">Good (cedar needs annual treatment)</td>
            <td class="py-2">Excellent (Thermowood low maintenance)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Heater included</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">No (sold separately)</td>
            <td class="py-2">Some models include heater</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Best for</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">Value, most budgets, any climate</td>
            <td class="py-2">Premium, wet/cold climates</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Almost Heaven: The Case For It</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">Almost Heaven has been making barrel saunas since the 1970s. They are the most-reviewed and most-purchased barrel sauna brand in North America, sold on Amazon with Prime shipping. Their Pinnacle 4-Person is the benchmark that every competitor gets compared against.</p>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">Western red cedar is a proven sauna wood — it handles heat and humidity well, smells great, and with basic annual treatment (cedar oil or wood sealant) lasts 15-20+ years outdoors. Most Almost Heaven owners never have a structural problem.</p>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-6">The 5-year structural warranty is also a meaningful advantage. Redwood Outdoors' 1-year warranty is short for a product at this price point.</p>

    <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white mb-8">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Almost Heaven Pinnacle 4-Person</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-3">The most popular residential barrel sauna in North America. Cedar construction, pre-cut panels, ships in about two weeks. Heater sold separately.</p>
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B017WJV8SO?tag=backyardsauna-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-block bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm">Check Price on Amazon</a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Redwood Outdoors: The Case For It</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">The Thermowood difference is real. Heat-treated Scandinavian wood has lower equilibrium moisture content than cedar, meaning it absorbs and releases moisture more slowly. In climates with heavy rain, salt air, or repeated freeze-thaw cycles, Thermowood holds up better over a 10-20 year period without requiring annual maintenance.</p>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">If you live in Seattle, coastal New England, or anywhere that sees 50+ inches of rain per year, the extra cost of Thermowood may be justified by avoided maintenance and a longer effective lifespan. Cedar in a wet climate without regular treatment starts greying and checking within 3-5 years.</p>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-6">The Panorama window model is also a genuine differentiator — no other mainstream brand offers a large panoramic window in a barrel sauna at scale.</p>

    <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white mb-8">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Redwood Outdoors Thermowood Barrel</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-3">Premium Thermowood construction, better long-term outdoor durability than cedar. $250 off available through our link.</p>
      <a href="https://www.redwoodoutdoors.com/collections/barrel-saunas" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" class="inline-block bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm">View on Redwood Outdoors ($250 Off)</a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Which Should You Buy?</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
      <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-1">Buy Almost Heaven if:</p>
        <ul class="text-stone-700 text-sm space-y-1 ml-3">
          <li>Your budget is under $4,000 total</li>
          <li>You live in a dry or moderate climate</li>
          <li>You want Amazon Prime shipping and easy returns</li>
          <li>You want a longer warranty</li>
          <li>This is your first sauna and you want proven, well-documented product</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-1">Buy Redwood Outdoors if:</p>
        <ul class="text-stone-700 text-sm space-y-1 ml-3">
          <li>Budget is $6,000+ and you want best-in-class materials</li>
          <li>You live in a wet, coastal, or high-precipitation climate</li>
          <li>You want low-maintenance outdoor wood long-term</li>
          <li>The panoramic window model appeals to your setting</li>
          <li>You want to avoid annual cedar maintenance</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="space-y-5">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">Is Redwood Outdoors or Almost Heaven better?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-700">Almost Heaven for value and warranty. Redwood Outdoors for material quality in wet climates. Both make good saunas — the right choice depends on budget and where you live.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">How much more does Redwood Outdoors cost?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-700">Roughly $4,000 more for Thermowood vs Almost Heaven's most popular model. That gap narrows somewhat with Redwood Outdoors' $250 buyer coupon.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-6 mt-10">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Related</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><a href="/brands/redwood-outdoors-sauna-review" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Full Redwood Outdoors Review</a></li>
        <li><a href="/brands/almost-heaven-sauna-review" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Full Almost Heaven Review</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/almost-heaven-barrel-sauna" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Almost Heaven Barrel Sauna Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/best-barrel-sauna-kits" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Best Barrel Sauna Kits</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/outdoor-sauna-buying-checklist" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Outdoor Sauna Buying Checklist</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
